Yes, it’s absolutely possible 👍 — and actually a very smart idea for learning both architectures side-by-side.

Short answer: No, it won’t create conflicts if you organize it properly.
But if you mix things carelessly, then yeah… IntelliJ + ports + dependencies can become messy.

