🧠 Will it cause conflicts?

👉 No conflicts IF you follow these rules:

🔹 Rule 1: Keep separate folders

Example structure:

ShreeBenakaSpace/
 ├── monolith-app/
 ├── microservices/
       ├── user-service/
       ├── content-service/
       ├── api-gateway/

👉 Open parent folder in IntelliJ, not individual projects randomly.

🔹 Rule 2: Use different ports

This is the #1 mistake people make.

Example:

Service	Port
Monolith	8080
User Service	8081
Content Service	8082
API Gateway	8080 OR 9000

👉 If ports clash → app won’t start.

🔹 Rule 3: Separate databases (or schemas)

You can:

Option A: Same DB, different schemas ✅
Option B: Separate DBs (better for microservices) ✅
🔹 Rule 4: Separate GitHub repos

